## Deploy

Prereqs:
- AWS CLI v2 authenticated (`AWS_PROFILE` pointing to an account with Bedrock enabled)
- `jq`, `zip`
- Python 3.11+ with `boto3`
- Model access granted in the Bedrock console for `{{ spec.model_id }}`
{%- if spec.ingress.type == "bda" %}
- Bedrock Data Automation enabled in the region
{%- endif %}

```bash
AWS_PROFILE=default AWS_REGION={{ spec.region }} bash scripts/deploy.sh
```

The script is idempotent — re-running it updates existing resources in place. All created ARNs are cached in `.deploy-state.json` (gitignored).

## Invoke

After deploy prints the `FLOW_ID` and `ALIAS_ID`:

```bash
FLOW_ID=<flow-id> \
ALIAS_ID=<alias-id> \
AWS_PROFILE=default \
python3 scripts/invoke_flow.py <case-id>
```

## Teardown

```bash
AWS_PROFILE=default AWS_REGION={{ spec.region }} bash scripts/teardown.sh
```

Deletes in dependency order: flow alias → flow versions → flow → agents → agent role → Lambdas → Lambda roles{% if spec.ingress.type == "bda" %} → BDA project → BDA blueprints{% endif %} → S3 bucket contents → S3 bucket.

## Layout

```
flow/                 Bedrock Prompt Flow graph (placeholders substituted at deploy)
{%- if spec.ingress.type == "bda" %}
bda/                  Bedrock Data Automation custom blueprints
{%- endif %}
{%- if spec.specialists %}
agents/               Agent instructions + OpenAPI action-group schemas
{%- endif %}
lambda/               Lambda handlers (one directory per function)
iam/                  Least-privilege policies (${AWS_ACCOUNT_ID} / ${AWS_REGION} rendered at deploy)
scripts/              deploy.sh, teardown.sh, invoke_flow.py
```
